Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Erected by Freemasons in 1904, The Lodge of Ancient Landmarks is an architectural gem most recently known for its offerings as a dining and event destination in Buffalo.

Built in the Beaux Arts style in 1904, The Lodge of Ancient Landmarks is a landmark in its own right with approximately 16,590 square feet of elegant space.

Visitors are greeted with white terra cotta ornamentation on the building’s exterior columns and roundels, surrounded by brick and hardwood throughout the welcoming atmosphere of Lucky Day Whiskey Bar on the first floor, and warm golden hues in a 350-person event hall on the second floor.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: A Beaux Arts Beauty in Buffalo
